||Preliminaires||
||	       ||	
|||||||||||||||||

The sampling time should be short enough, to reduce the nonlinearities in the problem [1].
When the prediction horizon becomes too short, the controller performance visibly degradates and the RTI solutions start to diverge from the converged solutions. [1]
High integration accuracies are not always needed and the closed-loop trajectories become insensitive to integrator accuracy when it gets high enough.[1]. Moreover, when deploying NMPC on real systems, unmodeled dynamics and external perturbations dominate over the integration error, so that it can be preferrable to favour faster sampling times and rather use a reduced integration accuracy in order to meet tight timing constraints. [1]

